title: Fixed cargo clippy, mostly derive Eq for PartialEq.
Update Cargo deps.
body: Occasional update.

title: Support arithmetic expression in the format command #46
body: Support binary operator `+-*/`, paren `()`, unary operator `-`.

title: Support Credit of fee, which appears when the transaction is withdrawn.
Add tests and renamed cond_else to branch.
body:
`cond_else` isn't intuitive and too long, renamed to `branch`.
Also added some unit tests.

title: Refactor parser
body:
* Refactor parser module into separated modules.
* Unit tests to be added, first let's merge it into main.

title: Support csv delimiter
body:
Improved several CSV features as a bundle.

* Support custom CSV delimiters.
* Support CSV with category.
* Support CSV with reversed order.

title: Introduce merge config feature
body:
Existing config YAML only assign one config into one path,
not supporting structured setup.
We can support merge for config so that common config can be shared between several paths.

title: Implement exchange rate information
body: This will allow to implement exchange rate annotation

title: Allow viseca input not to have processing fee line.
body:
Processing fee line seems to be omitted for really small amount
transaction.

title: Allow debtor to be optional in ISO Camt053, similar to creditor.
body:
As we already allow entry without related_party/creditor,
we'll also allow debtor to be missing.

title: Improve format accepting syntax
body:
Since `format` command was added with minimal parsing ability, it had several quarks about acceptable syntax.
Now it implements several syntax properly.
* preceding newline
* Balance validation syntax (` = 0`, ` = 1234 JPY`)

title: Separate data (semantics) module and repl (lexical) module.
body: This will unblock implementing fmt command.

title: Implement experimental format command.
body:
This can't parse many syntax supported by Ledger,
so it's still experimetnal.

title: Support Windows by path / CRLF.
body: Some tests were failing because of compatibility issue.

title: Account width larger than expected / double-byte characters
body:
* Cumulative minor fix related to cargo clippy warnings.
* Insert account / amount spacing (double spaces) even when the account is so long.
* Calculate the account column using unicode-width crate to support CJK characters.

title: Make transaction posting amount optional
body: At least posting amount should be optional for the formatting

title: Add multi currency support in CSV
body:
While ISO Camt053 has a currency support, CSV doesn't.
Implemented the currency support.

title: Update Rust version in CircleCI config.
Change CLI invocation, documented README.md.
body: We need to finalize CLI before sharing to the Qiita.

title: Support payback entry.
body: Negative entry should be supported.

title: Viseca support
body: Add viseca copy-n-paste text format.

title: Csv common platform
body: Use common extract platform for CSV as well.

title: Factor out generic extractor out of ISO Camt.053.
body:
Thanks to Rust lang forum, I could make it work without GATs.
https://users.rust-lang.org/t/how-can-i-write-a-generic-matcher/67621/13

title: Support Charges not included in ISO Camt053.
body: Support Charges which was originally excluded from the amount.

title: Update field semantics
body: Add some fields and make some ISO Camt fields optional.

title: Implement pending: true in rewrite rule.
body: Closes #25 .

title: Add balance verification to the output of ISO Camt 053.
body: balance is provided, so adding it is beneficial.

title: Ignore zero amount transaction charge.
body: It's zero so no need to be considered.

title: Support charge
body:
It'll add Chrgs (charge) support for ISO Camt import.
Also it'll add integration test.

title: Add functionality to support exchange rate on ISO Camt import.
body:
Currently it does convert ISO Camt import with exchange rate properly.
However it won't support charges, it should be implemented later.
It's not yet supported in CSV.

title: Add precision feature for the commodity.
body: Ensure minimal precision (such as `1.00` USD)

title: Config unification
body: Unify config to matcher-based.

title: Add initial ISO Camt 053 support
body:
This won't support any use-case, but it'll complete initial design.
Resolves #3.

title: Iso camt prerequistes
body: Introduce some prerequisite changes needed for ISO Camt053 format.

title: Add CI badge to README.
body: Add Travis CI badge to README

title: Implement amount based CSV
body:
This will support amount-based CSV, which is common for credit cards.

Resolve #6

title: Defines intermediate structure
body:
Current data::Transaction is the final output, mostly unnecessarily complex for just CSV or ISO CAMT import.
Fixed #4.

body: It doesn't have implementation, just config only.
